ZCZC OE74
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 042300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY EVENING A DPN LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM IS EXP TO BE CENTRED OVER
NERN SCOTLAND. OVERNIGHT THE LOW IS FCST TO MOV SLWY E/SEWARDS INTO THE
N SEA AND LIE 965 OFF THE E COAST OF DENMARK BY MIDDAY THURSDAY. ON FRIDAY
A SHALLOW LOW IS EXP TO MOV EWARDS ACROSS N FITZROY BISCAY AND CONTINENTAL
EUROPE. HIGH PRESSURE THEN BUILDS FM THE W BECMG CENTRED OVER BISCAY MIDDAY
SATURDAY AND EXTENDING A RIDGE NWARDS ACROSS THE UK. MEANWHILE A LARGE LOW
PRESSURE SYSTEM DEVELOPS TO THE W OF FITZROY. ON WEDNESDAY GALES OR NEAR
GALE FORCE WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS MUCH OF PORTPATRICK WITH SEV GALES POSS
IN MALIN HEBRIDES AND FAIR ISLE. WINDS ARE EXP TO GRADUALLY EASE FM THE
W FM MIDDAY THURSDAY BUT STRG TO NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS ARE EXP TO CONTINUE
IN THE NE THROUGH FRIDAY AND SATURDAY. ON SATURDAY STRG TO NEAR GALE FORCE
